The latter os these two is noticeable for its erratic orthography, remark- able even in an age of somewhat unsettled spelling. It has been found necessary to omit much of the contents of this account, but sufficient has been printed to justify these remarks. Some of the more peculiar orthographies in the omitted portions are cambores, campores (chambers), carlceares, carlcelmres (carriers), casse (causeway), crayl (gravel), llajgrolreyg (Hazlerig), lmygc (hedge), lavorerfflabourer), layng (‘ ling'), loyg· (load), lomnes (thorns).
